    "content": "**\"experience\"** as main translation for 经验, with \"empirical\" as contextual modifier.\n\nReasoning: The author almost never uses bare 经验 where it could be confused with 体验. The actual usage patterns are:\n\n- **经验性的** → \"empirical\" (adjective, no noun needed)\n- **经验的总结/预测/抽象** → \"empirical summary/prediction/abstraction\" (the \"empirical\" attaches to the compound, not to 经验 alone)\n- **个人经验** → \"personal experience\" (natural English)\n- **经验结构** → \"experiential structure\" (K1策略 line 205)\n\nIn almost every instance, 经验 appears in a compound where context already disambiguates. Writing \"empirical experience\" as a fixed two-word unit would produce awkward English: \"empirical experiential structure,\" \"personal empirical experience,\" \"summary of empirical experience.\"\n\nThe dictionary entry should read: **经验 → \"experience\" (epistemic/accumulated sense; render as \"empirical\" when adjectival 经验性的).** The disambiguation from 体验 is handled by the fact that they occupy different syntactic and semantic slots — the translator will not confuse them in practice."
